<br>
I just found out another necro bought the farm at 55, a friend of mine named Dethe, and now plays a Rogue. <br>
<br>
Verant's way of balancing Necromancers is to punish them in the higher levels.  Thanks VI. Meanwhile little do they know that they have ruined the class so much that most necro's make another character if they wish to continue. (Probably what they want)<br>
<br>
Gotta remember though, the warrior epic is two weapons...  1hs and 2hs.  And also, a warriors main duty is not damage dealing, it is damage taking. <br>
<br>
High level Rogues get fast, hard damage output.  In my opinion, they did make the rogue quest easy.  Especially since the hardest to obtain items were made 100% easier.  Course at the time, the robe of the Ishva was retarded.  a 12 hour spawn and a rare drop of the robe. Not to mention the kedge was nearly impossible to get as well. <br>
<br>
They need to readjust the quests in my opinion.  For me, I find it hard to believe that the epic necro weapon has a darkness effect same as Cascading darkness (Level 49 spell) and the quest robe has a small coffin summon corpse effect. <br>
<br>
Just as a cleric has a 56th manaless res, I think they should alter the necro epic for just that as well. <br>
<br>
Seems to me one thing though, whenever a class was having problems at one point, rogues a perfect example, they made it pretty uber.  Than you look at the necromancer which at one point its power was ridiculous, but than they nerfed it into a class which cannot even support its function to lifetap health back to regen mana on end encounters. <br>
<br>
To this day, a necro is, in my opinion, a class which can ride the bench.  I posted this on the DV site as well, but I can bring my Necro to a raid, camp him, play my warrior and will help the raid more with a tank...  Than log in Utnayan to summon if there are any problems. <br>
